# Integration Guide — AI ICU Vitals Model (v1.0)

## Purpose
This document explains how to run the inference API and the alarm, the input schema, example requests/responses, and notes for integration teams.

---

## Files included
- `models/vitals_model_tuned.joblib` — trained model artifact (joblib dict: {"model", "features"})
- `inference/` — inference API (predict.py, app.py) and `requirements.txt`
- `alarm_monitor.py` — local color-coded alarm simulation + desktop notifications
- `sample_data/vitals_combined_labeled.csv` — sample test data
- `metadata.json` — model metadata
- `README.txt` — quick start notes

---

## Input schema (JSON)
POST `/predict` expects JSON with these fields (all floats):

```json
{
  "heart_rate": 85.0,
  "bp_sys": 120.0,
  "bp_dia": 80.0,
  "spo2": 98.0,
  "temp": 36.7,
  "resp_rate": 18.0
}
v{
  "model_version": "vitals_model_tuned.joblib",
  "prediction": {
    "label": 0,
    "score": 0.12
  }
}